data.title: Mozart (1955 film)
data.meta_description: Mozart (also known as The Life and Loves of Mozart) is a 1955 Austrian drama film directed by Karl Hartl. It was entered into the 1956 Cannes Film Festival. The plot explores the mental state of Mozart during production of his final opera Die Zauberflte. Oskar Werner as Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart Joha
